Rice smugglers have invaded the Lagos port despite the Federal Government’s ban. The rice syndicates operating at the port, it was gathered, are working in convince with some Customs officials to divert the prohibited items to some of the bonded terminals in the Lagos metropolis, it was said. Some of the container loads of the rice diverted to a bonded terminal, findings revealed, have been evacuated by the Comptroller-General Strike Force Unit, Zone A, at a dedicated warehouse where the smugglers kept the foreign rice.   Tinubu promises to prioritise power, industrialisation,…     Police parade 37 suspects in Ekiti     Enugu advert agent held over offensive billboards   The coordinator, Comptroller-General Strike Force Unit, Zone A, Mohammed Yusuf, confirmed the diversion of the rice from the port and its seizure at a warehouse in Lagos by his unit. Yusuf said a large quantity of the foreign rice brought into the country illegally through the port has been evacuated by his unit from the warehouse where the smugglers kept them after diverting the containers to a bonded terminal. Yusuf said most of the rice was “brought in by unscrupulous importers who operate in some bonded warehouses without payment of duty, adding that the warehouse where the consignment was stored had been sealed.